problems.title: Create and Display a Singly Linked List (SLL)
problems.description:
Problem Statement
You are given N integers. Your task is to create a Singly Linked List (SLL) by inserting elements at the end. After creation, display the linked list elements.

Time Complexity
Creating the list by insertion at end and displaying takes O(N) time.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer N.
The second line contains N space-separated integers.

Output Format
Print the elements of the linked list separated by space.

Example
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
Output:
10 20 30 40 50
Explanation: Insert elements at end and then display final linked list.
problems.constraints:
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
Values may be negative or positive
Expected Time Complexity: O(N)

problems.title: Insert Node at End (SLL)
problems.description:
Problem Statement
You are given N integers. Your task is to create a Singly Linked List (SLL) by inserting each element at the end. After inserting all elements, display the final linked list.

Time Complexity
Each insertion at end takes O(1) if tail pointer maintained, so total O(N).

Input Format
The first line contains an integer N.
The second line contains N space-separated integers.

Output Format
Print all elements of the linked list separated by space.

Example
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
Output:
10 20 30 40 50
Explanation: Insert each element at end and display the final linked list.
problems.constraints:
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
Values may be negative or positive
Expected Time Complexity: O(N)
hintsList: Maintain a tail pointer for O(1) insertion at end.
Move tail = tail.next after linking new node.

problems.title: Delete First Node (SLL)
problems.description:
Problem Statement
You are given N integers to create a Singly Linked List (SLL) by inserting elements at the end. Your task is to delete the first node of the list and then display the remaining list. If the list becomes empty after deletion, print -1.

Time Complexity
Deleting the first node takes O(1). Building and printing the list takes O(N).

Input Format
The first line contains an integer N.
The second line contains N space-separated integers.

Output Format
Print the updated linked list elements separated by space. If the list becomes empty, print -1.

Example
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
Output:
20 30 40 50
Explanation: Delete the first node and display the rest.
problems.constraints:
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
Values may be negative or positive
Expected Time Complexity: O(N)
hintsList: Deleting first node means moving head to head.next.
If the list has only one node, output should be -1.

problems.title: Delete Last Node (SLL)
problems.description:
Problem Statement
You are given N integers to create a Singly Linked List (SLL) by inserting elements at the end. Your task is to delete the last node of the list and then display the remaining list. If the list becomes empty after deletion, print -1.

Time Complexity
Deleting the last node takes O(N) since traversal is required to reach the second last node.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer N.
The second line contains N space-separated integers.

Output Format
Print the updated linked list elements separated by space. If the list becomes empty, print -1.

Example
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
Output:
10 20 30 40
Explanation: Delete the last node and print the remaining nodes.
problems.constraints:
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
Values may be negative or positive
Expected Time Complexity: O(N)
hintsList: To delete last node, traverse to second last node and set its next to NULL.
If head == NULL or head.next == NULL, result becomes empty.
